The paper deals with video captioning, which involves understanding both visual and textual information. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel approach that uses Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) and attention mechanisms, which are popular techniques in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on large-scale benchmark datasets of videos, which suggests that it could also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
